### Source 2 — PSA Philippine Statistical Yearbook (PSY), Chapter 2: Income and Prices
**URL:** https://psa.gov.ph/philippine-statistical-yearbook
**Direct download (2023 PSY, Chapter 2 Excel):** https://psa.gov.ph/system/files/psy/2_2023.xlsx

This is PSA's annual statistical compendium. Chapter 2 is a single pre-formatted Excel workbook containing key income and poverty tables consolidated from multiple surveys.

**File format:** XLSX. Single file, direct download, no portal interaction. The workbook contains multiple sheets organized by table number. Rows use merged cells for region headers; footnote rows are embedded inline. Some cleaning is needed before analysis.

**Granularity:** Primarily national and regional. Provincial detail is present but less complete than the full OpenSTAT tables. HUC breakdowns are not included in this source.

**Update frequency:** Published annually, but poverty data only refreshes every three years with the FIES. The 2023 PSY reflects the same 2021 poverty figures as OpenSTAT until the 2024 PSY edition incorporates the 2023 FIES data.

**Coverage check against the problem statement:**

| Project KPI | Available in this source? | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Poverty incidence by region | ✅ Yes | Regional level only; less granular than Source 1 |
| Per capita poverty threshold | ✅ Yes | Regional level |
| Income gap | ✅ Yes | Regional level |
| Province-level breakdown for Caraga | ⚠️ Partial | Some provincial rows present, not all |
| Magnitude of poor families | ✅ Yes | Regional level |

**Known gaps and limitations:**
- Provincial-level detail for Caraga's five provinces is incomplete in the PSY — using Source 1 is required for the Caraga deep-dive.
- Excel layout requires preprocessing: merged headers, footnote rows interspersed with data rows, and inconsistent region-code formatting must be resolved before the file is usable.
- The PSY is published once annually. The 2024 edition (which will include 2023 poverty data) was not yet available at the time of this assessment.

