### Source 3 — PSA Small Area Estimation (SAE) Poverty Statistics
**URL:** https://psa.gov.ph/statistics/poverty-sae
**Data file:** https://psa.gov.ph/statistics/poverty-sae/stat-tables

This is a separate PSA release that uses the Small Area Estimation technique to generate poverty incidence estimates at the municipality and city level — below the provincial granularity of the main FIES tables.

**File format:** XLSX (one file per release cycle, containing all 1,611 cities and municipalities).

**Granularity:** Municipality and city level — the finest geographic detail available for poverty data in the Philippines.

**Update frequency:** Tied to the FIES cycle. 2018 and 2023 SAE releases are available. No 2015 or 2021 SAE data.

**Coverage check against the problem statement:**

| Project KPI | Available in this source? | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Poverty incidence by region | ✅ Yes (aggregated) | Primary purpose is municipality level |
| Province-level breakdown for Caraga | ✅ Yes | All Caraga municipalities present |
| Butuan City trend | ⚠️ Two points only | 2018 and 2023 — insufficient for a trend line |

**Known gaps and limitations:**
- Only two data points are available (2018 and 2023) — not enough for a trend analysis on its own.
- Not a replacement for Source 1 at regional or provincial level; intended as a supplemental drill-down.
- Will be incorporated in Weeks 8–12 for the Caraga province deep-dive section, not as a primary analysis source.

